      "span_text": "It seems likely that the substantial polygenic component involves SNPs that are not distributed randomly across the genome but are distributed across genes that share a common biological function or pathway. [8] Recent pathway analyses provided evidence for the importance of the cell adhesion molecule pathway in schizophrenia, as well as the glutamate metabolism, transforming growth factor-b signaling and tumor-necrosis factor receptor-1 pathways. Pathway analysis is predicated upon accurate pathway definitions and validated assignment of genes to pathways."
